WEBVTT

00:32.738 --> 00:43.669
Welcome back, and we are still in Proverbs 7, and we're going to read verses 22 through 27, Proverbs chapter 7.

00:45.590 --> 00:47.152
So let's get started.

00:48.833 --> 01:01.906
Suddenly follows her as an ox goes to the slaughter, or is one in fetters to the discipline of a fool, until an arrow pierces through his liver as a bird hastens to the snare

01:02.210 --> 01:04.954
so he does not know that it will cost him his life.

01:06.115 --> 01:12.164
Now therefore my sons, listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

01:13.165 --> 01:16.410
Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways.

01:16.530 --> 01:18.553
Do not stray into her paths.

01:19.514 --> 01:24.601
For many are the victims she has cast down and numerous are all her slain.

01:25.102 --> 01:30.930
Her house is in the way of shield descending to the chambers of death.

01:32.706 --> 01:33.827
Let's go to the Lord in prayer.

01:37.111 --> 01:51.786
Father, we read this passage and Lord, my heart trembles at the dangers that are in this world.

01:53.228 --> 02:02.578
It's temptations and Lord that many men and women

02:03.842 --> 02:18.581
Many youths have fallen as a result of the evil one who is like a roaring lion seeking who he may devour, as a result of listening to the world and its temptations.

02:20.504 --> 02:31.698
Father, I pray for those who will listen to this short devotional Lord that they will not mock

02:32.834 --> 02:50.760
or think that I'm exaggerating, that they would recognize that you would show them the dangers of sin, the need to cling to Christ, the need to saturate their lives in the Word of God.

02:53.444 --> 02:56.268
Father, help us now as we go into this text.

02:58.271 --> 03:00.274
In Jesus' name, amen.

03:01.698 --> 03:22.949
When you look at verse 22, you see that the consequences of sin can be very, very severe and ox being slaughtered, a man being marched off in fetters, possibly to his death, an arrow piercing through the liver, a bird trapped in a snare.

03:24.352 --> 03:31.442
And, you know, of all the things, I think that would be terrifying.

03:31.522 --> 03:34.967
is we look at this bird trapped in a snare.

03:35.267 --> 03:36.629
No one should think about that for a moment.

03:37.270 --> 03:43.219
When a bird is snared, usually by the foot or the wing, they're very conscious.

03:43.379 --> 03:46.023
I mean, they're aware that they're trapped.

03:47.245 --> 03:55.677
And I always think about that, to being caught in a trap, keenly aware and having to wait.

03:55.777 --> 03:59.282
Because sometimes when you set traps, or as a little boy, you set traps,

03:59.522 --> 04:05.569
You go back to those traps, you know, in 24 hours and 36 hours.

04:06.650 --> 04:10.454
And so to be captured and know you're captured.

04:11.075 --> 04:14.078
And now you have to wait and wait and wait.

04:14.759 --> 04:15.239
You're doomed.

04:16.220 --> 04:20.145
And then you hear the footsteps approach of the hunter.

04:21.987 --> 04:23.929
And there's nothing that you can do about it.

04:25.270 --> 04:28.754
That's the severity of what's being said here.

04:29.058 --> 04:31.381
And that's the reason for the warning in verse 24.

04:31.762 --> 04:36.328
Now therefore my son listened to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

04:38.712 --> 04:44.200
We had a lot of cattle, but there was one in particular, wasn't even a bull.

04:45.682 --> 04:49.127
It was a cow and her brand was U-14.

04:50.529 --> 04:55.256
I mean, I was a little boy and I still remember that cow, U-14.

04:56.077 --> 04:56.978
She was mean.

04:57.890 --> 05:03.237
She was worth a lot of money, but she was mean.

05:03.337 --> 05:05.841
If she hadn't been worth money, my dad would have put her down.

05:08.885 --> 05:10.307
She got my mom one time.

05:12.530 --> 05:13.952
Several times she almost got me.

05:13.972 --> 05:19.559
And I remember when my dad first pointed her out, he says, you need to be careful with that one.

05:20.220 --> 05:22.423
And like, I'm not paying much attention.

05:22.443 --> 05:23.905
You have to be careful with everything.

05:24.286 --> 05:25.788
And he goes, no, boy, listen to me.

05:26.769 --> 05:27.570
She'll get you.

05:28.194 --> 05:30.877
she will get you.

05:31.858 --> 05:35.501
So you have to be extraordinarily careful with that cow.

05:35.521 --> 05:39.465
Even when you're on horseback, you need to be careful with this one.

05:40.666 --> 05:44.250
And I remember just how serious he looked in his face.

05:44.330 --> 05:49.515
And I mean, it communicated to me, Hey, this is one to watch out for.

05:49.795 --> 05:51.577
Well, that's what's going on here.

05:51.617 --> 05:57.202
Now, therefore my sons listen to me and pay attention.

05:57.314 --> 06:00.238
to the words of my mouth.

06:00.378 --> 06:01.960
Now, I want you to look at something.

06:02.621 --> 06:21.085
Now, it says, based on how deadly this is, he says, now, after all that I've explained to you about how deadly this sin is, about how it can destroy your life, about how it can destroy you in eternity, based on all that.

06:21.125 --> 06:21.906
Now,

06:22.786 --> 06:29.133
So you're never, you're never really going to respond correctly unless you understand how deadly sin is.

06:29.634 --> 06:31.636
And he's done everything to explain it.

06:31.896 --> 06:45.391
And he says, now based on that, listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth and do not let your heart turn aside to her ways and do not stray into her path.

06:45.411 --> 06:48.114
And verse 24, listen to me, pay attention.

06:49.186 --> 06:50.408
You realize what's going on here.

06:50.428 --> 06:52.110
It's kind of like a Hebrew parallelism.

06:52.170 --> 06:54.954
He's stating it and then he's stating it again.

06:55.014 --> 07:02.644
He's just repeating it in a little bit different way in order to bring out more meaning and to draw attention to how serious this is.

07:04.647 --> 07:08.712
He says, give heed to what you have learned.

07:08.833 --> 07:12.818
Now, one of the things that's important here is

07:15.010 --> 07:17.794
If you were sitting with me right now and you were shaking your head.

07:17.834 --> 07:18.095
Yes.

07:18.175 --> 07:18.415
Yes.

07:18.496 --> 07:18.736
Yes.

07:18.856 --> 07:21.340
I'd go, you know, you shake your head all day long.

07:22.782 --> 07:24.024
Uh, not appreciate that.

07:24.405 --> 07:34.341
But if you don't listen, if you don't actually live this, if you don't actually respond to it, if you just say, yes, it's true.

07:36.624 --> 07:37.366
It's not enough.

07:38.047 --> 07:39.930
You have to really feel it.

07:41.051 --> 07:42.674
You have to have a sense

07:43.042 --> 07:45.085
of danger around sin.

07:45.606 --> 07:45.946
You do?

07:46.427 --> 07:59.145
Just like my dad was telling me, when you get near that cow, when you get in the same pin with her, you, beyond the alert, all your senses need to be firing because she'll get you.

08:00.407 --> 08:01.448
All right, it's the same way here.

08:01.468 --> 08:04.212
It's not just enough to say, oh, yeah, I understand.

08:04.933 --> 08:07.076
No, you need to feel it.

08:07.497 --> 08:10.962
Now, here in verse 24, he said, listen,

08:11.586 --> 08:19.153
In the Bible, this almost, this almost always carries the idea of listen and obey.

08:19.554 --> 08:21.255
It's two sides of the same coin.

08:21.556 --> 08:26.000
If you don't obey, you haven't listened and you really need to understand that.

08:27.181 --> 08:29.323
That's why your parents will tell you something.

08:29.964 --> 08:31.886
You'll, you'll ascend to it.

08:31.986 --> 08:32.286
Yes.

08:32.466 --> 08:32.846
Okay.

08:32.967 --> 08:35.309
And then you'll go violate what they told you.

08:35.329 --> 08:35.989
And what do they say?

08:36.029 --> 08:37.251
Didn't you listen to me?

08:38.852 --> 08:40.754
Listening in the scripture.

08:41.090 --> 08:42.953
implies obedience.

08:42.973 --> 08:44.175
Two sides of the same coin.

08:44.235 --> 08:46.659
You can't have one without the other.

08:47.019 --> 08:51.647
And then he comes back and he not only says, listen, he says, pay attention.

08:52.147 --> 08:55.833
We've looked at this word several times, but it's worth revisiting it.

08:56.334 --> 09:02.103
The idea here is that of you're leaning into it.

09:03.485 --> 09:03.986
Okay?

09:05.218 --> 09:14.192
You're trying with all your mental faculty to understand what's being said and understand the significance of it.

09:14.252 --> 09:17.297
It's the idea of expenditure of mental energy.

09:17.638 --> 09:18.359
It's focus.

09:19.561 --> 09:22.265
Someone says, look, it's a life-death situation.

09:22.625 --> 09:26.131
You need to listen to me and then you start leaning in.

09:26.191 --> 09:28.094
You're focusing.

09:28.314 --> 09:29.176
That's the idea.

09:29.216 --> 09:30.578
It's like,

09:30.818 --> 09:38.731
When, when you see a deer or something in the field and it's way, way off and you're hunting with your son and you go, there he is.

09:39.833 --> 09:43.539
And the boy can't see it and you go, look, there it is.

09:44.661 --> 09:52.754
Or when you're shooting with a bow, you, you lean in because you're concentrating everything that you have on that target.

09:53.736 --> 09:56.761
He's saying, look above all things.

09:57.021 --> 09:57.682
Listen to me.

09:58.946 --> 10:00.328
And this is so important.

10:00.348 --> 10:06.978
You know most people, most young people, most old people, they begin their day, they just get out of bed and take off running.

10:09.242 --> 10:10.784
That's a very dangerous thing to do.

10:12.767 --> 10:27.570
Your priority ought to be knowledge of God and knowledge of God's Word and knowledge of God's guidance through this very, very dangerous minefield of a life, okay?

10:28.066 --> 10:30.670
Now he says, listen, pay attention.

10:31.411 --> 10:32.933
And then what else does he say?

10:34.195 --> 10:35.838
Guard your heart and your feet.

10:35.998 --> 10:38.762
Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways.

10:39.623 --> 10:45.131
Do not stray into her path, her paths.

10:45.592 --> 10:48.877
Well, when it says paths, realize she's walking around all over the place.

10:49.338 --> 10:51.321
There's danger everywhere.

10:51.781 --> 10:55.026
Now the heart here in verse 25,

10:55.330 --> 11:00.176
The heart refers to the control center, your control center.

11:00.397 --> 11:04.642
It controls your will, your emotions, your actions.

11:06.225 --> 11:14.215
Now, it's always, listen to me, it is always a matter of the heart.

11:15.297 --> 11:18.441
If you guard your heart, your feet will follow.

11:18.781 --> 11:22.386
If you guard your heart, your hands will follow.

11:22.722 --> 11:25.746
If you guard your heart, your speech will follow.

11:26.146 --> 11:28.169
It's always a matter of the heart.

11:28.329 --> 11:30.692
Guard your heart.

11:32.474 --> 11:33.275
And how do you do that?

11:33.916 --> 11:37.040
First of all, you may say, well, how do I do that?

11:37.160 --> 11:38.382
I do it by reading the word.

11:38.502 --> 11:38.762
No.

11:40.645 --> 11:44.129
First of all, you do it by not listening to certain things.

11:46.212 --> 11:50.056
And then by listening to others, you do not listen to the world.

11:50.096 --> 11:51.378
You listen to God.

11:52.226 --> 12:21.234
Because you see it doesn't matter how many times you take a shower if you keep jumping in a sewer You keep jumping in the sewer you may have to take a shower 25 times a day and you're still filthy Yes, I want you to read the word I want you to memorize the word I want you to meditate on the word let the word of God be a lamp unto your feet But if soon as you're leaving the word you're just going and contaminating yourself on your iPhone or your computer and

12:21.506 --> 12:28.175
or getting into ungodly conversations or you're in relationships with people who are going to have a negative impact on you.

12:28.195 --> 12:36.507
I'm not going to say the word won't have an impact because it will, but what I will tell you is it'll have less of an impact.

12:36.527 --> 12:38.690
So guard your heart.

12:38.930 --> 12:41.313
It's always a matter of the heart.

12:42.595 --> 12:50.706
I've written here, if you turn your feet to the path of sin, it is because you have already turned your heart away from God.

12:51.682 --> 12:52.724
Let me read that again.

12:52.764 --> 13:05.022
If you turn your feet to the pack of sin and your hands to doing sin and your mouth to speaking sin, it is because you've already turned your heart from God.

13:05.443 --> 13:06.744
Guard your heart.

13:07.926 --> 13:09.529
Guard your heart.

13:10.831 --> 13:17.741
You know, I was traveling to the airport the other day and you know, you have to be careful when you're walking through an airport.

13:17.781 --> 13:18.482
You know why?

13:18.850 --> 13:23.095
because everyone is walking and still looking at their phone.

13:23.115 --> 13:24.978
And I mean, they will flat out run you over.

13:26.019 --> 13:27.320
It is an addiction.

13:27.801 --> 13:30.905
It is horrific what's going on.

13:33.388 --> 13:48.146
And everything that's being pulled up, that is contrary to the word of God, it's turning your heart from God, and which means it's eventually turning everything else about you.

13:48.482 --> 13:49.043
from God.

13:49.984 --> 13:51.265
Now, how do we guard our heart?

13:51.886 --> 13:53.268
Psalms 1 19 11.

13:54.449 --> 13:58.995
Your word, I have treasured in my heart that I may not sin against you.

14:00.637 --> 14:01.678
It's pretty simple, isn't it?

14:03.661 --> 14:04.622
Let's just reverse it.

14:05.343 --> 14:10.930
Your word, I have not treasured in my heart so that I may sin against you.

14:17.026 --> 14:22.034
I heard a preacher one time say, if I'm not in the word one day, I know it.

14:23.356 --> 14:25.960
If I'm not in the word two days, my wife knows it.

14:26.421 --> 14:29.786
If I'm not in the word three days, my associates know it.

14:30.768 --> 14:35.996
If I'm not in the word four days, everybody knows it.

14:37.338 --> 14:42.086
Psalms 37, 31, the law of his God is in his heart.

14:43.087 --> 14:44.690
His steps do not slip.

14:45.474 --> 14:47.236
Why do his steps not slip?

14:48.157 --> 14:50.260
Because the word of God is in his heart.

14:52.182 --> 14:58.730
Look, I remember one time I said something and a guy, he was really sarcastic.

15:00.832 --> 15:10.504
I said one of the great necessity of the day, the thing that would promote holiness among God's people is just to spend time in the word and prayer.

15:11.805 --> 15:12.626
And he said,

15:12.930 --> 15:16.135
Well, that's kind of a simplistic solution, don't you think?

15:17.236 --> 15:18.458
I said, well, let me ask you a question.

15:18.478 --> 15:20.821
How much time do you spend in the Word of God in prayer?

15:23.084 --> 15:24.867
He really couldn't give an answer.

15:25.888 --> 15:27.110
I said, enough said, isn't it?

15:28.853 --> 15:33.079
You know, the Christian life really honestly is not that complex.

15:34.420 --> 15:34.821
It's not.

15:36.003 --> 15:38.907
It's difficult, but it's not that complex.

15:39.528 --> 15:41.170
There's no song we used to sing.

15:41.250 --> 16:04.146
Even when I was a kid in church trust and obey for there's no other way to be happy in Jesus, but to trust and obey Learn the word trust the word obey the word Again, enough said So few people actually spend any significant time

16:04.226 --> 16:05.187
in the Scriptures.

16:05.588 --> 16:16.721
Young person, if you want to be extraordinary, not just in the ministry, not just in church, but in every aspect of life, then you need to get in the Word of God.

16:17.802 --> 16:22.107
Even if you go to a great church with a great preacher, that's not enough.

16:22.808 --> 16:25.191
First of all, the greatest preacher is just a man.

16:26.593 --> 16:30.898
You need to come in direct contact with infallible Word.

16:31.138 --> 16:33.481
And that is only found in the scriptures.

16:33.941 --> 16:42.290
You know, even listening to me, you have the responsibility to study the word and ask yourself, what brother Paul is saying?

16:42.891 --> 16:43.392
Is it true?

16:46.415 --> 16:49.138
I want to communicate truth.

16:49.599 --> 16:50.980
I want to be sincere.

16:51.000 --> 16:56.306
I want to be a true teacher, but I'm just a man.

16:59.074 --> 17:07.663
You owe it to yourself, but you also owe it to me to study the Word of God so that when I need correction, you can correct.

17:08.063 --> 17:14.369
So that if I say something that's not right, you can discern it and realize it has no binding on you.

17:15.791 --> 17:18.794
You must study the Word of God.

17:19.395 --> 17:26.802
Now, I want to, I want to end right there and

17:28.322 --> 17:30.084
Because I want you to realize something.

17:31.045 --> 17:48.184
The only way you're going to avoid the calamity of this young man is to saturate your life in the Scriptures.

17:49.306 --> 17:52.509
You ever seen a towel saturated with water?

17:52.970 --> 17:56.594
You pick it up, water is dripping out of it everywhere.

17:57.570 --> 18:04.940
That's the way you need to be, that the Word of God is just your life.

18:06.422 --> 18:14.733
Young people, there's a lot of people today and they love the Lord, but all they talk about is how many books they've read.

18:14.773 --> 18:27.090
Now I've read a few books myself and I appreciate good books, but all the books in the world added up are nothing compared to the Scriptures.

18:27.490 --> 18:29.233
and studying the scriptures.

18:29.633 --> 18:36.664
No book has the power to change you, transform you like the scriptures.

18:37.926 --> 18:41.832
I could quote off many authors right now that I greatly appreciate.

18:41.952 --> 18:54.331
Charles Spurgeon, Martin Lloyd Jones, John Flaval, John Owen, Jonathan Edwards, sermons of Whitfield, Robert Murray McShane, his memoirs, Samuel Rutherford.

18:54.932 --> 18:56.114
There are so many

18:57.666 --> 18:59.609
They can't hold a candle.

19:01.752 --> 19:05.697
They can't hold a candle to the inspired Word of God.

19:09.382 --> 19:14.209
If you want to have power for life and ministry, then make the Word of God.

19:17.113 --> 19:19.376
Your food.

19:20.818 --> 19:21.359
Let's pray.

19:23.862 --> 19:26.546
Father, thank you for the Word.

19:27.778 --> 19:45.080
And I pray, Lord, that you would create an insatiable hunger for the Word of God in your people, especially for those young people who are listening to this teaching.

19:46.642 --> 19:49.546
I ask this in Jesus' name.

19:49.566 --> 19:49.746
Amen.

